    "A variety of approaches have been explored, with generative adversarial networks (GANs) being a pioneering model introduced in 2014.",
    "GANs involve a generator creating realistic images and a discriminator distinguishing between generated and real images.",
    "Over the past decade, these models have evolved significantly, as illustrated in the provided images showing the progress in generative image model capabilities.",
    "Diffusion models, introduced in 2015, follow an iterative forward diffusion process to systematically destroy structure in a data distribution.",
    "They then learn a reverse diffusion process to restore lost structure, offering controllable generative capabilities."
